gov.va.vinci.leo.tools

Class LeoProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.vinci.leo.tools.LeoProperties
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Client, Service

    public abstract class LeoProperties
extends Object
    Handles loading Properties from the leo.properties file including setting defaults initially and storing values we expect from that properties file.
    Author:
    thomasginter

        protected String mDescriptorDirectory
        The path to the directory where descriptors will be generated. By default this path is null as descriptors are generated in the tmp directory of the system.

      • mCasPoolSize

        protected int mCasPoolSize
        CAS pool size determines the max number of requests that can be outstanding.

      • mFSHeapSize

        protected int mFSHeapSize
        FS heap size in bytes of each CAS in the pool.

      • mTimeout

        protected int mTimeout
        Timeout period in seconds. If a CAS does not return within this time period it is considered an error. Default is wait forever.

      • mInitTimeout

        protected int mInitTimeout
        Initialization timeout period in seconds. If initialization request does not return within this time it is considered an error. Default is 60 seconds

      • mCCTimeout

        protected int mCCTimeout
        CAS complete timeout in seconds. Once all CAS requests are complete a collection process complete command is sent. Default is wait forever

      • mJamServerBaseUrl

        protected String mJamServerBaseUrl
        The base url for the Jam (JMX Analytics Monitoring) server if available.

      • mJamQueryIntervalInSeconds

        protected int mJamQueryIntervalInSeconds
        If registering with JAM, what is the monitor query interval in seconds. default is 60*60 (1 hour)

      • mJamResetStatisticsAfterQuery

        protected boolean mJamResetStatisticsAfterQuery
        If registering with JAM, should statistics be reset after each gather? Default is true.

      • mJamJmxPort

        protected int mJamJmxPort
        If registering with JAM, this is the port the local JMX Server will listen on. If this is -1, the service will find and use a local open port.

      • mDeleteOnExit

        protected boolean mDeleteOnExit
        Should the generated XML descriptors be deleted on program exit? Default is true.

      • loadprops

        public void loadprops(String propertiesFile)
               throws Exception
        Load the properties file specified by the user. Supported properties: brokerURL casPoolSize ccTimeout deleteOnExit deploymentDescriptor descriptorPath endpoint fsHeapSize initTimeout jamJmxPort jamQueryIntervalInSeconds jamResetStatisticsAfterQuery jamServerBaseUrl serviceName timeout
        Parameters:
        propertiesFile - Path to the properties file to be loaded
        Throws:
        Exception - If unable to load the properties file

      • loadprops

        protected void loadprops()
                  throws Exception
        Load the properties from the properties file that will be used for execution.
        Throws:
        Exception - if the properties file cannot be found or loaded.

      • loadProperties

        protected void loadProperties(Properties properties)
                       throws FileNotFoundException
        Load the properties from a properties object. Note, properties that are in the properties object, but not one of the below, are just ignored. Supported properties: brokerURL casPoolSize ccTimeout deleteOnExit deploymentDescriptor descriptorPath endpoint fsHeapSize initTimeout jamJmxPort jamQueryIntervalInSeconds jamResetStatisticsAfterQuery jamServerBaseUrl serviceName timeout
        Parameters:
        properties - The properties object to get properties from.
        Throws:
        Exception - if the properties file cannot be found or loaded.
        FileNotFoundException
